sql:
SELECT COUNT(disease_id) 
FROM patient_diagnoses 
WHERE status = 'resolved';

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT patient_id) 
FROM patient_diagnoses 
WHERE status = 'resolved';

external_knowledge:
- "Latest ailment" refers to the most recent diagnosis for each patient;
- "Still active" refers to the current status of the diagnosis being 'active';
- "Signs of improvement" refers to the outcome of the most recent treatment being 'improved'.

- 'Garden of active diagnoses' refers to patients with ongoing health issues;
- 'Blossoms of improved outcomes' refers to cases where the treatment has resulted in patient improvement;
- 'Watered more than once' refers to patients who have received more than one treatment.

- "consulted the doctor" refers to having at least one consultation appointment;
- "battling more than one active ailment" means having more than one active disease diagnosis;
- "disease prevalence rate" is the estimated rate of the disease in the population.

- Anxiety disorders are a group of mental health conditions characterized by significant feelings of anxiety and fear;
- Comorbidity refers to the presence of one or more additional disorders co-occurring with a primary disorder;
- 'Unchanged' in the context of treatment outcomes means the patient's condition has not improved or worsened after the treatment;
- Psychiatrists are medical doctors who specialize in mental health and can prescribe medications and provide therapy.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM treatments 
WHERE outcome = 'improved';

external_knowledge:
- 'Flowers of anxiety disorders have blossomed' refers to patients diagnosed with anxiety disorders;
- 'Gather the names and stories' means to collect patient names, disease names, and recommended treatments;
- 'Tales of their medical journeys' refers to the medical histories and the dates they were recorded;
- 'Treatments prescribed' includes the names of treatments, their start and end dates, and the providers who administered them;
- 'Gardeners of health' refers to healthcare providers.
